<div id="my-modal" class="modal">
    <header class="header">
        <h2>Popup Source Instructions</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="body" style="overflow:auto;height:calc(100% - 68px)">
        <h3>Intro</h3>
        <p>
            Popups use auto-generated HTML in order to render your signup form and don't require any
            intervention unless you'd like to custom style them.
        </p>
        <h3>HTML</h3>
        <p>This will render a form with the following HTML:</p>
        {% set htmlCode =
'<div data-source-code="' ~ source.shortcode ~ '" class="lb-popup lb-status--success">
    <div class="lb-popup-background"></div>
    <div class="lb-popup-container">

        <a href="#" class="lb-popup-close">
            Close
        </a>

        <form method="POST" class="lb-form" data-ajax-enabled="1" data-has-consent="1">
            <input type="hidden" name="action" value="list-builder/signup/store">
            <input type="hidden" name="source" value="' ~ source.shortcode ~ '">
            {{ csrfInput() }}

            <div class="lb-popup-image">
                <img src="/path/to/your/selected/image.jpg">
            </div>

            <div class="lb-popup-content">
                <div class="lb-title">Your title</div>
                <div class="lb-text">Your additional text</div>

                <div class="lb-form-row lb-form-row--input">
                    <input class="lb-input lb-input--email" type="email" id="email-9999"
                        name="email" placeholder="Your Email">
                </div>

                <div class="lb-form-row lb-form-row--checkbox">
                    <input type="hidden" value="0" name="consent">
                    <input class="lb-checkbox" type="checkbox" id="consent-9999" name="consent" value="1">
                    <label class="lb-checkbox-label" for="consent-9999">
                        I consent to receive information about services and special offers by email.
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="lb-form-row lb-form-row--buttons">
                    <button class="lb-submit" type="submit">
                        Subscribe
                    </button>
                </div>

                <div class="lb-success-message">
                    Your success message
                </div>

                <div class="lb-error-message">
                    Any applicable error message
                </div>

            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>
' %}
        <pre><code>{{ htmlCode|escape }}</code></pre>
        <h3>Styling</h3>
        <p>You can chose to leave your popup unstyled, in which case you can use
        the HTML above as a guide for styling. Alternatively you can select a pre-made
        theme whilst configuring the Source. Attaching a theme to a popup simply adds an
        additional class to the wrapping <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>.</p>
        <p>It is perfectly acceptable to apply a simple theme and then tweak the css
        by overiding the applied styles using either <code>!important</code> or
        greater css specificity (I've tried to keep my css nesting to a minimum).</p>
    </div>

</div>
